Subject: Development Update: Mobile Optimization, UI Enhancements, and Branding Refinements


Please find below a summary of the latest design and development updates implemented on the homepage. All changes have been successfully committed and pushed to the main branch.

1. Comprehensive Mobile Optimization (Homepage)

Responsive Layouts: Extensively optimized all homepage sections (Hero, Bento Boxes, Shop Carousel, Inspiration Banner, and Contact Form) to ensure seamless rendering across mobile devices.
Fluid Scaling: Adjusted spacing, margins, and flex/grid layouts to prevent content overlap and ensure a smooth vertical flow on smaller screens.
Typography & Navigation: Implemented auto-scaling for headings/text for better readability and refined the mobile hamburger menu for an improved user experience.
2. Brand Identity Update

Navbar Logo: Replaced the legacy "Jacket Masters / JM" branding with the new company name "The Design Factory / TDF" across the navigation bar.
3. Premium UI & Visual Enhancements

Glassmorphic Overlays: Addressed text visibility issues on the dark images in the "Specially Curated for Adults" section by implementing a premium frosted-glass (blur) pill effect, complete with a dynamic brand-color (pink) hover transition.
3D Detail Pop-up (Shop Section): Refined the UI for the "Read More" product detail modal. By reducing the height of the background container in both CSS and the GSAP animation logic, the product image now intentionally overlaps the top and bottom edges, creating a highly modern 3D pop-out effect.
4. "Our Inspiration" Section Updates

New Inspiration Banner: Integrated a new full-width hero banner ("Cappuccino - Our Inspiration") directly above the Contact section. The background of the provided image was seamlessly blended (mix-blend-mode) into the site's cream theme (#f3ece4) with refined typography.
Bento Box Media: Updated the "Our Inspiration" card within the Bento section by replacing the placeholder image with the finalized Beagle asset.
5. Version Control / Deployment

Git Push: All the above features and mobile optimizations have been pushed to the GitHub repository and are ready for the upcoming client pitch.
